Ultimate squad (or star?) goals! 

Webb has captured NGC 602, a young star cluster 200,000 light-years away in the Small Magellanic Cloud. This cosmic nursery shows star formation in conditions similar to the early universe, helping us unlock secrets of how stars are born.
